			<head>Biographical Note</head>
			<p>Thomas Lee Scott was born in 1820 in Independence, Texas. A farmer by trade, he lived
				in Washington County, Texas with his wife Mary E. Scott. In the 1850s the family
				owned slaves. During the American Civil War Scott served as a soldier in the
				Confederate Army. He was granted amnesty after the war ended in 1865.</p>
		</bioghist>
		<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
