			<head>Scope and Contents</head>
			<p>Financial documents, civic records, and personal correspondence compose the Thomas
				Lee Scott Papers, 1834-1865. Materials relating to the American Civil War include
				Confederate war tax receipts, military orders, and Thomas Lee Scott’s signed Amnesty
				Oath. Scott’s civilian life is represented by a dinner invitation from Miss A. R.
				Holmes and bills of sale for the purchase of slaves from John L. Young and Mary E.
				Coles. The collection also features an undated poem signed by J. C. Hill and an 1834
				marriage bond between John Thompson and Jane A. Gossett.</p>
		</scopecontent>

